<body>
<p>An simple statement. Should be empty style:</p>
<boxed-text>
  <statement>
  <p>This material is normally indented.</p>
  </statement>
</boxed-text>
<p>A statement of the kind <monospace>corollary</monospace>, which is
defined in the defaults.</p>
<boxed-text>
  <statement>
  <label>
  <p>Corollary</p>
  </label>
  <p>This is a corollary. The kind is defined by default.</p>
  </statement>
</boxed-text>
<p>A statement of the kind <monospace>principle</monospace>, which has
to be created on the fly.</p>
<boxed-text>
  <statement>
  <label>
  <p>Principle</p>
  </label>
  <title>
  <p>Quine's principle</p>
  </title>
  <p>Everything is something.</p>
  </statement>
</boxed-text>
<p>An horizontal line within a statement:</p>
<boxed-text>
  <statement>
  <p>All is one.</p>
  <p>One is less.</p>
  <hr/>
  <p>All is less.</p>
  </statement>
</boxed-text>
</body>
